This tasted like a hot buttered rum without alcohol. The word "rum" in the name made it less of a hit at my church function, but those who tasted it were in love. I took the extra home, heated it, added water and rum, and had a hot buttered rum. Yummy. The only issue was that the cinnamon got swollen, grainy, and clumped. I would probably use a cinnamon stick instead next time, or add the cinnamon at the end.

